begin_memory_text: We did introductions, chatted about where we're from and the general conditions and weather. She mentioned her career in the past as a driver and we talked about driving in winter and snow in Michigan
middle_memory_text: She talked about her past doing daycare, her family and grandkids, what it takes to get daycare licensed and what that entails, fostering and adopting children and how her daughter lives with her and isn't able to have kids and she wants to do that too but it would be difficult to give the child back up to a bad situation
end_memory_text: She told me about real estate prices in her area and I in my area, she told me how she sold her condo to pay for her son's mortgage because the bank backed out on them and now she's renting a place. She just switched to contacts because she works in a cold room making sandwiches and he glasses were fogging up. Then we talked about covid in our respective areas
rest_of_day_open: Today is my day off so I've gotta do some grocery shopping and take care of some household matters like switching out my shower head. Thursday and Friday I'll work and I'm going to see my Grandma on thursday also, should be good to see her. Then it's the weekend! I don't have any big plans for the weekend but I'll probably try to go for a hike. I've been really depressed but I'm trying to make some positive changes.
critical_positive: The conversation worked well because we are both pretty friendly and warm in our attitudes, we were both smiling and seemed happy to talk to each other. I enjoyed hearing about her life experiences and it's comforting to talk to and have the perspective of an older person. I'm a good listener and she seemed to enjoy talking so that worked. The pace felt pretty good.
critical_negative: At times it seemed like my conversation partner was talking quite a bit at length without stopping to ask me questions or include me in the conversation but after a while she seemed to circle back with a question to me. A few times we accidentally cut each other off but not to badly.
